<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/116> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #116" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "First Interrex (Dion. Hal. 8.90.4-5; cf. Lyd. Magg. 1.38, where he is mistermed Dictator)." ;
	dprr:hasID 116 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/104> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #104" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Festus 180 L." ;
	dprr:hasID 104 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/103> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #103" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A curious and broken notice in Festus (180 L) mentions a wide stone paving and the burning near the Circus of a number of persons, whose names, partially preserved, for the most part agree with names in the consular Fasti. Val. Max. (6.3.2) mentions a P. Mucius, Tr. Pl., who burned his nine colleagues for conspiring with Sp. Cassius (cf. Dio fr. 22; Zon. 7.17), but no authority places the number of Tribunes of the Plebs at ten so early. As the names are almost all patrician and consular, it remains uncertain to what incident or what losses in the Volscian Wars the passage of Festus refers." ;
	dprr:hasID 103 .
